AIM :
To develop a mathematical model and simulate the speed–torque characteristics of a DC
motor used in drone propulsion using simulation software and analyze motor behavior
under different load conditions. Done in simulink matlab

Simulation Procedure :
1. Open the simulation software
2. Create a new model workspace.
3. Insert the DC motor model.
4. Add voltage source to supply input voltage.
5. Connect mechanical load to the motor shaft.
6. Add sensors to measure motor speed.
7. Set motor parameters.
8. Apply different load torque values.
9. Run the simulation.
10.Observe speed–torque characteristics

The simulation results show that the speed of the motor decreases when the load torque
increases. This relationship represents the typical speed–torque characteristic of DC
motors. Understanding this behavior helps in selecting suitable motors for drone
propulsion systems. 
